<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-02-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-02-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="7" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d7">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">855.413/18a</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-02-13">February 13, 1929</date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 191</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: As you are doubtless aware, the American
                            Battle Monuments Commission established by Act of Congress in March
                                1923<note n="14" xml:id="d7fn14">42 Stat. 1509.</note> contemplates
                            undertaking certain work of a memorial nature in Belgium. You are
                            accordingly requested to extend all possible assistance to the
                            Commission’s representatives in order to facilitate their work.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. R.
                                    Castle</hi>, Jr.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>